Step 1: Determine Total Revenue from the income statement.  
• Total Revenue = 5,695,115.02

Step 2: Get the Total Assets at the beginning and end of the period from the balance sheet.  
• Beginning Total Assets = 13,000,000.00 (on 2023-12-31)  
• Ending Total Assets = 15,023,526.85 (on 2024-01-28)

Step 3: Calculate the average total assets.  
• Average Total Assets = (Beginning Total Assets + Ending Total Assets) / 2  
  = (13,000,000.00 + 15,023,526.85) / 2  
  = 28,023,526.85 / 2  
  = 14,011,763.425

Step 4: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio by dividing Total Revenue by the Average Total Assets.  
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Total Assets  
  = 5,695,115.02 / 14,011,763.425  
  ≈ 0.406  
Rounding to two decimal places gives approximately 0.41.

Thus, the Total Asset Turnover Ratio is approximately 0.41.
